column5: LOOKING FOR FISH REPORT NEAR MORSON LOTW?

Big Fish, I got back from a week on LOTW out of Morson on Saturday 8/14. Walleye fishing was good pulling spinners w/minnows, caught fish on both weed lines and rock reefs. Also did lots of casting for pike/muskie with mixed results. As usual, when we had overcast skies fishing was much better. Lagrest pike was 15#, lots of muskie follows but none caught. We even spent a half day fishing crappies in Miles bay with ok results. Tight Lines !!
Slow... Eyes were very tough to find. Pike not bad along weed lines. 40, 34, 28, 26, 26, and smaller for the Pike
